Cloud communication platforms have revolutionized the way organizations communicate by offering a wide range of solutions and services. The market can be segmented based on offerings into solutions and services. Solutions segment includes voice over internet protocol (VoIP), application programming interfaces (APIs), interactive voice response (IVR), Unified Communications as a Service (UCaaS), and others. On the other hand, the services segment consists of professional services and managed services. Furthermore, based on organization size, the market is bifurcated into small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) and large enterprises. In terms of end-users, the market caters to various industries such as healthcare, BFSI, IT and telecom, retail, government, education, and other sectors.

